item.description:
Hey friends,
Welcome to #AzureSpringClean, an initiative from Joe Carlyle and Thomas Thornton where I&rsquo;m honored to be able to participate in again for the 4th year already. Thanks guys for trusting me once more for sharing some Azure knowledge&hellip;
This time, I wanted to try and guide you through the buzzword of the last couple of years, containers&hellip; and more specifically, what different options you have in Azure to run your containerized workloads.

Hi all,
This is one of the nail biting challenges of our industry, failing in running a straight-forward task. Especially when it is failing&hellip;
What happened? I was creating a pipeline in Azure DevOps to deploy an ARM template for VM setups with VM Extensions. To prep this deployment, the artifacts (DSC scripts) should be copied to Azure Blob Storage, in order for the Azure DevOps build agent to &ldquo;find&rdquo; it.

Only about a month ago, I decided to move my former website (running on Wix) to the Open Source Hugo platform, running it as a static website with MarkDown, using Azure Storage Static Website. For more details on how to do this, have a look at my blog post here
I have to say, it runs fine, is cheap, fast, reliable,&hellip;
But then I discovered the new Azure Static Web App capability, as announced during //Build conference earlier this week, so I wanted to give it a try.
